Analysis: To improve the UX of the page, I will implement two concrete changes:
1. **Last Updated Indicator & Sticky Header**: Users currently don't know exactly when the data was fetched. Adding a timestamp gives confidence in real-time monitoring. Making the header sticky ensures the refresh button is always accessible even when scrolling through long explanatory content.
2. **Actionable Error State**: When data fetching fails, instead of just telling the user to refresh the page, providing a clear "Retry" button directly inside the error message reduces friction and keeps them in the flow.
